o	(\Pi_{\text{geo}}) is surjective onto (SO(3,1)) (or its double cover),
o	the kernel acts only on “internal” directions,
o	null directions in (V) lift to a well-defined null subset in (W).
That already tells us something important:
Not all of (SO(9)) can be “physical”—you need a physical subgroup (G_{\text{phys}}) whose action respects a Lorentzian structure on a 4D quotient or subspace.
